summary:
The Security Council,
Recalling previous resolutions and statements on the Democratic Republic of Congo (DRC), 
Determined to promote peace process at national level and facilitate establishment of inclusive transitional government,
Expressing concern over fighting and atrocities in Ituri and humanitarian situation in Bunia,
 Reaffirming support for Ituri Pacification Commission’s political process and swift resumption,
 Recognizing urgent need for secure base for Ituri Interim Administration,
 Commending MONUC’s efforts to stabilize Bunia and support political process,
 Authorizes deployment of Interim Emergency Multinational Force in Bunia until 1 September 2003 
to stabilize security and humanitarian situation, protect airport and internally displaced persons;
Stresses temporary basis of force, authorizes Secretary-General to reinforce MONUC presence;
 Calls on Member States to contribute personnel, equipment and resources; 
 Authorizes force to take necessary measures; 
Demands parties cease hostilities, respect humanitarian law, and cooperate with force and MONUC;
 Condemns killing of MONUC personnel and humanitarian staff; 
 Requests regular reports on implementation of mandate.
